itemListElement.name: 10 Hours Private City Tour in Seattle - Chartered Tour

name: 10 Hours Private City Tour in Seattle - Chartered Tour
description:
Exceptional 10-Hour Seattle day tour: Customization, Comfort & Flexibility
· It offers personalized itineraries, allowing you to customize your 10-hour tour of Seattle according to your preferences.
· You'll have a dedicated driver who is familiar with the city, ensuring a smooth and efficient journey.
· The vehicle is well-maintained and comfortable, providing a pleasant travel experience throughout the day. 
· Our service focuses on flexibility, enabling you to make spontaneous stops and explore the hidden gems of Seattle that might not be on a typical tourist route.
· This combination of customization, expertise, comfort, and flexibility truly sets our transport apart for an unforgettable 10-hour in Seattle.

itemListElement.name: Traditional Japanese Ramen Cooking Class in Seattle

name: Traditional Japanese Ramen Cooking Class in Seattle
description: Embark on a culinary journey with a talented chef as you dive into the world of Japanese ramen. In this hands-on cooking class, you’ll learn to craft the perfect bowl of ramen by blending soy sauce and miso for a rich, flavorful broth. You’ll also discover how to cook tender pork and soft-boiled eggs, essential components of the dish. With guidance from an expert chef, you’ll master the art of seasoning and garnishing your ramen with fresh herbs, ensuring each bite is a harmonious combination of flavors. Whether you're a ramen enthusiast or a culinary beginner, this class offers the perfect opportunity to bring the authentic taste of Japan into your own kitchen. Get ready to enjoy a warm, comforting bowl of ramen made from scratch!

itemListElement.name: Evening Colors Sunset Sail Tour in Seattle

name: Evening Colors Sunset Sail Tour in Seattle
description: Sailing aboard Seattle's premier tall ship is the best way to see our city from the water. Help hoist the sails, then we will shut the engine down and enjoy the quiet of our beautiful schooner cutting through the tranquil Puget Sound Waters. Enjoy a beverage as the sun sets beyond the Olympic Mountains. We may even fire our cannon to salute another amazing summer day!

review.name: Great experience
review.reviewBody: This was the highlight of our Seattle trip! The views of the skyline and sunset over the water were absolutely stunning. The crew was friendly, knowledgeable, and made the whole experience relaxing and fun. A peaceful, picture-perfect way to end the day—highly recommend!

review.name: Sunset Cruise
review.reviewBody: As a local resident I've done the tour a few times over the last couple of years & always have an amazing time on board. The Bay Lady is a beautiful ship, the crew is friendly, attentive & informative. I've done other harbor cruises & it's nice to not have the recorded narratives. The crew answers any questions you might have though while mingling with the guests. We were lucky to see Orcas off in the distance on this cruise. Thank you Capt. Anthony, Madison, Clark, & Nick for a lovely sunset cruise! Definitely will be back this season!

review.name: Excellent evening cruise
review.reviewBody: The crew were great, drinks priced right and the views were amazing. It was very educational as well. I definitely recommend this trip.

review.name: Wunderschön
review.reviewBody:
Eine wunderschöne Tour auf einem wunderschönen Segelboot. Ich habe die Tour im Sonnenuntergang sehr genossen. Wir hatten dazu  einen warmen Sonnentag bei strahlend blauem Himmel. 
Der einzige Kritikpunkt: Das Boot war gut belegt. Es wäre sicherlich angenehmer gewesen mit drei bis fünf weniger Passagieren. Man saß doch sehr sehr beengt. Und auch der Platzwechsel an der Reeling gestaltete sich eher umständlich. Aber dann wäre die Tour sicherlich automatisch teurer. Trotzdem, es lohnt sich. Ich habe den Törn sehr genossen.

review.name: Awesome
review.reviewBody: Tour was a great experience.   Staff were friendly and knowledgeable and the scenery was awesome.  I would recommend this to anyone coming to Seattle.

review.name: Spectacular Sailing
review.reviewBody: What a beautiful night for a sunset cruise. As the sun set, the city looked like GOLD! Our captain, Nick and his crew were so amazing, energetic and fun. They made the evening perfect. Could not ask for a better experience. Don't miss the Tall Ship if you are ever in Seattle.

review.name: Great ride and crew. Worth it for the views
review.reviewBody: The view was amazing and rude was very relaxing. The crew was fun and very helpful in every way. I can't recommend this enough.

review.name: Fabulous night and fantastic crew
review.reviewBody: Well, it was an amazing weather day for our sailing trip. The crew was energetic and passionate about their work. They were engaging with the customers. The weather was nothing short of amazing so it made for a perfect evening. Great sunset.

review.name: Stunning sunset when the weather cooperates
review.reviewBody:
Loved the sunset cruise.  Crew was pleasant and service was good.  I had excellent weather and enjoyed a great view of Mt. Rainier, partial rainbows over the Seattle skyline, and a fantastic sunset over the mountains opposite the sound.  Crew said we had one of the best sunsets of th season.  If you book, hope the weather is just as great for you.

As a perk, they offer non-alcoholic and alcoholic beverages for purchase.

review.name: Beautiful and amazing
review.reviewBody: My significant other and I had a wonderful time. It was beautiful the crew was amazing. They even provided blankets if you got to cold because of the breeze. They use the engines to get you out of the pier then ask patrons to help set the sails and you sail around for a bit. The views where amazing. We got a beautiful sunset and a rainbow. Everyone on the crew was friendly. They made a point to all come and chat with us. They offered drinks as well.

itemListElement.name: Seattle Sightseeing City Tour with Hotel Pick-up

name: Seattle Sightseeing City Tour with Hotel Pick-up
description: Sit back and relax while our professional guides showcase the best of Seattle. Enjoy a door-to-door experience with hotel pickup and drop off included. Learn about everything from Seattle's history to the current shape of Seattle.

review.name: Seattle overview
review.reviewBody: The guide Erika was fantastic and full of great information and insight. Drives great also and very friendly. Great overview of all the important places in Seattle in 4 hours.

review.name: A lovely way to see Seattle
review.reviewBody:
A lovely way to see the sights of Seattle. We were also lucky the weather was kind. 

Would very highly recommend for all ages and abilities.

review.name: Great Introduction and Overview of Seattle
review.reviewBody: Fun and relaxing tour of Seattle.  Tyler was a fantastic guide. He was very knowledgeable and easy going. The mini bus picked us up at our hotel and off we went all over the City and into some suburbs. We were able to stop and walk around in some areas, see some of Seattle’s most famous places, learn lots of interesting history, visit a local fish shop at a marina, view Puget Sound and the City from a high overlook, and see some beautiful residential areas.  This was a great and stress free way to learn about Seattle.  Thank you, Tyler!!!

review.name: Informative
review.reviewBody: Tyler was so informative, we learned so much about Seattle and surrounding areas, neighborhoods, waterways. Will certainly use this tour company on other vacations.

review.name: Great tour and excellent tour guide/driver. Would highly recommend.
review.reviewBody:
We had a lovely day on our tour. Our driver Ken, we were given a brief geography lesson on Seattle before heading off to see the sights. He took us to all the attractions listed where possible (there were some road closures) and gave a good talk about each area or attraction. 
Great tour and excellent tour guide/driver. Would highly recommend.

review.name: Great first experience of Seattle
review.reviewBody: Great overall introduction to the city and its history and neighborhoods. Our guide, Lucinda, was very knowledgeable, and we were fortunate to have a sunny clear day with the ability to see Mt. Rainier and the Olympic range clearly.

review.name: Amazing!
review.reviewBody: We were picked up from our hotel. Fantastic tour of Seattle love. Wonderfully informative and we were dropped off at Pike Market Place. Couldn’t have asked for a better experience.

review.name: Beautiful Seattle
review.reviewBody: The views were amazing.  Seattle is beautiful and this trip enabled us to see the most important sights as we only had two days in Seattle. Fantastic Host

review.name: Unlocking Seattle's Secrets: A Memorable Journey with Lucinda
review.reviewBody:
A Delightful Seattle Discovery with Lucinda

My recent Seattle tour with Lucinda was an absolute highlight of my visit to the Emerald City. Her expertly crafted itinerary took us through Seattle's most iconic locations with perfect timing and engaging commentary.

At Pike Place Market, Lucinda shared fascinating stories about its 1907 origins and the market's evolution while we watched the famous fish-throwing tradition. The Queen Anne Hill stop offered breathtaking city views, where she explained Seattle's great fire and subsequent rebuilding on top of the original city.

The Hiram M. Chittenden Locks provided a unique perspective on Seattle's maritime history, watching boats navigate between Puget Sound and Lake Union while learning about the ingenious fish ladder system. Lucinda's knowledge of the area's Native American heritage, logging history, and tech boom transformation was impressive.

Her engaging storytelling style, attention to detail, and obvious passion for Seattle made this tour exceptional. I highly recommend booking with Lucinda for an unforgettable Seattle experience.

review.name: Great experience
review.reviewBody: It was a great tour around the city with historical facts. Ron was a great guide and brought a lot of enthusiasm. Would do agai!

name: 2-Hour Seattle Sailing Harbor Tour
description:
Seattle's Tall Ship welcomes you aboard for a day sail on our classic schooner! Our Harbor Sailing tour is family-friendly and is an excellent way to see the Seattle skyline, the beauty of the Puget Sound, even mountain views! We will depart from our dock at Pier 66 Bell Harbor Marina, then set our sails for a 2-hour cruise in the Puget Sound.

We also have an amazing sunset sail! Don't forget to check that one out too!

review.name: Great sail!
review.reviewBody: Wonderful way to start our vacation!! Crew was great.  Knowledgeable, fun and friendly.  Highly recommend for all ages.

review.name: Enjoy sailing
review.reviewBody: It was a wonderful experience. Never been on a sail ⛵️ before but enjoyed it a lot. Views of Seattle, Mt. Ranier and the area all around were amazing. The crew was friendly and engaging.

review.name: Pleasant way to see Seattle Harbour
review.reviewBody: The crew were fantastic and extremely helpful and it was a fun trip sailing around Seattle harbour for a couple of hours. I had mobility issues and they arranged a wheelchair to get me along the dock and everyone had comfortable seating. Drinks are able to be purchased on board and we found the young crew to be engaging and knowledgeable about the boat and experiences. It is a very pleasant way to see Seattle from the water, although if you’re going expecting to see anything other than the harbour, you will be disappointed! Like many trips, it’s what you make of it and we really enjoyed our trip.

review.name: Boring
review.reviewBody:
Departed on time and they had very courteous staff, but it was a very  BORING sailing for 2 hours. No narratives or explanations about what we were seeing around (ground or sea), where we went, nor what should be expected.. Simply, we got on board & sailed around quietly for 2 hours and then came back..  

The staff kindly gave out blankets for those who felt cold, but -as advertised- every drink was for fee including hot drinks & water.

review.name: Loved Every Minute
review.reviewBody: Great trip, probably the highlight of our long weekend in Seattle. Enjoyed taking part in raising the sails and had some great views of the city, the islands and the sunset. The wind was cold and the crew were very prompt in providing blankets. Worth every penny.

review.name: Great
review.reviewBody: My wife and I went on the two hour trip. Great time. Nice views of Seattle and a nice boat ride. The crew is fantastic. They make this more than just another boat ride. Even the weather was nice.

review.name: A great time!
review.reviewBody: The experience was great. Being out on the water sailing was a fantastic experience. The crew was friendly, engaging, and truly wanted us to have a good time. They were very professional and knowledgable in their handling of the boat - we felt confident they knew what they were doing and it was a safe trip.

review.name: Spectacular Adventure
review.reviewBody: An amazing sail through the harbor, not crowed, could move around the boat freely, and the crew were so friendly and informative. Loved it and highly recommend!

review.name: Sailing on a tall ship!
review.reviewBody: Awesome experience! Sailing on a tall ship is a lot of fun!  Crew of three young gentleman very capable and experienced with sailing the vessel. Also, very nice, polite and informative.

review.name: Beautiful Sites and a great crew made for a perfect morning on the water!!
review.reviewBody: We had a blast seeing the sound, it was a great time for conversations and they had a great crew who made sure everyone old and young got a chance to help raise the sails!!

name: Private Seattle Cocktail Culture Tour
description:
If you’re going to have a cocktail in Seattle, why not have one with us in the center of the universe? Come try out some city classics and local spirits on this cocktail tour of Fremont, Seattle’s funkiest neighborhood.

Whether or not you’re an aficionado, your guide will start you out with the basics, with a couple of tastes of spirits produced right here in state. We’ll then move on to full cocktails that we hope will make your taste buds sing!

Cocktail number one might be a Seattle classic or a creation specific to the neighborhood, its history, or its community. As you enjoy your libation, your guide will fill you in on the long history of booze in the Northwest, from the days of Prohibition to the modern-day booming cocktail scene Seattle’s become since the 90s. 

Along the way, you’ll find some landmarks scattered throughout the neighborhood, seemingly out-of-place objects – including the famous Fremont Troll – that have truly defined Fremont as the “Center of the Universe”.

review.name: Very good tour
review.reviewBody: A very good tour of Seattle Center.   We loved specially the Space Needle tower.   Our guide Sam was very nice, patient  and excellent.

review.name: Seattle Cocktail Tour
review.reviewBody: The tour was informative - lots of history about Seattle intermixed with different types of cocktails.  Lee obviously had done a lot of research and was well prepared. He kept the tour moving and interactive; he was personable and made everyone feel comfortable.  I enjoyed the various cocktails and knowing their ingredients.  Excellent guide and tour of the Pioneer Square area.

review.name: private and tasty cocktail tour
review.reviewBody: We were lucky to be the only Guests on this tour, so my wife and myself had the guide just for us. It was just great. There's no chance to make this experience on your own! Lee knows a lot about the places we were and the cocktails as well. The drinks were excellent. Be sure not to have an empty stomach when you participate. If you are planning to make this tour, we cross our fingers that you will get Lee as your Guide. We had so much fun!

review.name: Great drinks, great companions
review.reviewBody: Great drinks, great info! Wouldn’t have found these places on my own and never would’ve known where/how these drinks originated. Fingers crossed you also get Lee.

review.name: Best tour ever
review.reviewBody: Such an amazing tour with an even better guide we had a blast! I would say if you are looking for some great history for the city and some great drinks. This is the tour for you.

review.name: Fun adventure while learning
review.reviewBody: Didn’t know anything about the existence of such a tour, till I came across the Facebook Ad. And I’m glad, I did it with my friends. Not only did I learnt about the hidden gems in Pioneer Square (Marble Room), I also learnt a lot of buffets about cocktails from the guide, Lee. Not only was Lee knowledgeable, he also took time to learnt each of our likes n dislikes, and ordered cocktails based on those parameters. 3-hours well spent, learning stuff while having fun

review.name: Learned a lot!
review.reviewBody: This was my first time ever attending a Seattle tour. I honestly thought it was going to be a bit boring but I was honestly surprised. Our little group was humorous, and outgoing. Lee was very knowledgeable on the drinks and had recommendations for the best bars in Seattle. He was training someone at the time, and she was also very knowledgeable on Seattles underground city. So it was almost 2 tours in 1. Thank you all for such an amazing time!

review.name: What an enjoyable cocktail afternoon!
review.reviewBody:
We throughly enjoyed our cocktail tour with Lee. Lee was very knowledgeable, attentive and shared his insights of Seattle history and cocktail choices.

My husband enjoyed the marble bar especially the care and attention that were invested in the cocktails served. 

At the third venue, Lee used his initiative to choose cocktails based on first and second venues selection as the chosen choices were not available and remembered our taste buds.

review.name: Solid Seattle Cocktail Tour!!!
review.reviewBody:
Wow! What a amazing tour!!!

I came in with a big group of buddies (11 of us in all) for a bachelor party and we had a great time with our guide, Lee. The tour entailed a nice walk to 3 bars where we got to try drinks based off general flavor profiles.

Our guide would ask, “do you want to try something ‘tropical’ OR a ‘pick-me-up’? Something ‘strong and refreshing’ OR ‘light and floral’?” This helped my group branch out a bit into trying other kinds of cocktails we may have not otherwise ordered on our own.

Lee was super knowledgeable and engaging, and just did a solid job herding such a large group of rowdy guys. We loved the process overall.

Thank you, Lee!

review.name: We had an excellent time in this tour! Lee our tour guide was very knowledgeable and gave us the best experience!
review.reviewBody: We loved trying all the different coffees and learning the different coffee cultures and exploring! Highly recommend!

name: Seattle Coffee Crawl-Small Group Tour
description:
Explore the vibrant Capitol Hill neighborhood with a local tour guide and where you'll savor excellent Seattle coffee! 

On this Seattle walking tour, you’ll discover the origins and intricate flavors of Seattle’s finest coffee beans. You'll also indulge in trendy and delicious coffee creations crafted by talented Seattle baristas. Each stop on our tour is handpicked to showcase the city's innovative coffee culture, providing a perfect blend of traditional and contemporary coffee experiences.

Discover why Seattle's coffee scene is so renowned and why coffee is an integral part of life in the Pacific Northwest. Our expert guides will share insights into the historical significance and cultural impact of coffee in Seattle, offering a deeper appreciation for this beloved beverage.

Book your Seattle coffee tour today and immerse yourself in the rich coffee heritage of Capitol Hill, experiencing firsthand the passion and creativity that make Seattle a global coffee capital.

review.name: Great Coffee!
review.reviewBody: Sam is amazing!!! Def will recommend this tour with him to my friends! My fav stop was the ghost alley where we got the Lush life!

review.name: I learned so much about coffee - and the tour guide is great!
review.reviewBody: My wife and I decided to take this coffee tour during our trip to Seattle because we knew coffee was significant to the city (and my wife just loves Starbucks). We learned so much during this tour and from Lee, the tour guide! His knowledge of the city and the history and manufacturing of coffee was impressive! If we had the time, I would have happily taken this tour a second time because of how much I learned and I would have prepared more questions for him about coffee! Absolutely recommend it.

review.name: Sam was awesome!
review.reviewBody: Only a day in advance, my fiance and I booked the Seattle Coffee Culture Tour and it was everything we wanted in a coffee tour experience. My fiance and I are looking to become more knowledgeable about coffee and processing coffee, and our tour was incredibly well thought out and informative. Mostly because our tour guide, Sam Osborn, was FANTASTIC! Seriously--because we booked it last minute and the tour was on a Monday, my fiance and I were the only ones. We're pretty quiet people, and I was worried it was going to be awkward, but Sam was so kind, so charismatic and really really informative and inclusive. We learned so much about coffee, down to the anatomy of the bean, to history of coffee businesses in Seattle. The tour was MORE than I expected; we also learned about the history of Seattle and Capitol Hill in general, which was an awesome plus for us tourists. We can't thank Sam enough for such an incredible tour and a memorable experience. He was simply awesome.

review.name: Great experience
review.reviewBody: Great time to go try new things. Sam was an awesome host. Very knowledgeable, my favorite part was the last shop but the drink was so good as well.

review.name: So good!
review.reviewBody: Awesome tour with Sam! Very knowledgeable, friendly, and kind. The coffee and treats at each stop were all so god we couldn’t decide what we liked best. Definitely recommend this tour for anyone interested in coffee and goodies.

review.name: Coffee adventure in Seattle.
review.reviewBody: Excellent tour! Great conversation and coffee. We were very grateful for the local recommendations. Informative and interactive with adaptation for personal preference.

review.name: Drank coffee and enjoyed bakery treats
review.reviewBody: Great tour, knowledgeable and informative guide from Sam! He was very personable, and made the experience more enjoyable

review.name: When in Seattle…
review.reviewBody: Sam was our fun and informative guide! I learned a bunch and have a renewed interest in coffee, especially how it’s roasted and where it’s grown! Loved the cafes we visited. My favorite treat was the mocha macaron from MeeTea Cafe. Favorite coffee was the Lush Life coffee cocktail at Ghost Note Coffee! Thanks, Sam, for a great tour!

review.name: Great experience
review.reviewBody: The tour moved along at a decent pace, neither too slow nor too fast. Our guide, Sam, was knowledgeable and had a good sense of humor. I enjoyed it and I don’t even like coffee.

review.name: Great tour with Sam!
review.reviewBody: Really great tour! Different styles of coffee to please everyone and delicious bakery good also. Sam was an amazing tour guide who not only had information about our samples and the establishments but about the history and process of coffee as well.  Would highly recommend!

itemListElement.name: Seattle History Tours & Civil War Seattle Tours

name: Seattle History Tours & Civil War Seattle Tours
Seattle Salmon Fishing Trips
description:
Based just 5 miles from downtown Seattle, Wind Knot Salmon Guides will make you feel like you’re on another planet. Come and explore the riches of the Puget Sound, where you’ll sail across the bays against stunning backdrops doing battle against one of the Pacific Northwest’s most prized fish – Salmon.

Step aboard the 25’ Grady White Gulfstream cuddy cabin and see for yourself! This vessel can cater to up to 5 anglers or 1200 lbs and features a toilet. Bring your own drinks and snacks onboard and settle in for an exciting day of fishing.

From May through early June, you’ll be bottom fishing these waters, while other months are strictly reserved for Salmon. Using light gear, you’ll “mooch” the waters with fresh or frozen bait. This style of fishing is suited best for physically fit anglers.

review.name: A memory to last a lifetime
review.reviewBody:
My dad has been a hobby fisherman his whole life, and taught me how to fish as a child. The memories of fishing together at various hidden lakes in the Cascades have always held a special place in my heart, so for my dad's 60th birthday I thought I'd return the favor by taking him on a special fishing trip.

I am so grateful to Wind Knot for making our father & daughter fishing adventure everything I hoped it would be. Thank you so much Captain Dave!

review.name: Exceeded expectations
review.reviewBody: I grew up on the water near Seattle and been on multiple guided excursions, but learned more about fishing and the Sound in one, four hour trip than all previous experiences combined. Captain Dave is an extraordinary host and highly recommend Wind Knot.

itemListElement.name: Snoqualmie falls and Twin Falls Hike

name: Snoqualmie falls and Twin Falls Hike
description: What makes this tour unique is that I am focused on keeping you very well entertained and educated while we make our way to the gorgeous Twin Falls and Snoqualmie Falls. The ride to the Falls and back is full of information about the Pacific Northwest as well as entertaining stories, a whole Lotta fun facts and a bit of comedy. I’ve been a naturalist Guide for nearly 20 years, and I have refined the content of my tours to maximize enjoyment and education! I am very passionate about our planet, consciousness, and all things paranormal and supernatural. Ladies, if you are looking for a tour that will keep your husbands or boyfriends thoroughly entertained with content about UFOs, aliens, Bigfoot, and many other mysterious and intriguing paranormal activities. This is the tour for you!

review.name: Great guide, beautiful trail
review.reviewBody: Jared was great! Very knowledgeable in all things in the Pacific Northwest. We learned a great deal and enjoyed our hike in Twin Peaks. The trail is pretty doable and you get plenty of time.  He provided great recommendations for local eateries and other things to do. Would definitely book with him again.

review.name: Great hike and great views!
review.reviewBody: We had such a great time on this tour! And Jared is a delight. We enjoyed chatting with him, and he was an excellent guide. The hike to Twin Falls was beautiful and easy. If you hike all the way to the falls it gets a little more strenuous at the end, but nothing too hard. It’s worth it! And Snoqualmie Falls is gorgeous. So beautiful! That part is not a hike. Just a little jaunt to the overlook. Highly recommend!

review.name: Awesome tour
review.reviewBody: The tour we previously booked cancelled and I’m so glad it did! Jared was very knowledgeable about the area and also funny and entertaining. My boyfriend and I had a great time!! The hike was easy as well and perfect for beginners.

review.name: Perfect Tour
review.reviewBody: Our tour exceeded our expectations.  Jared was extremely knowledgeable and gracious.  We had time to explore on our own.  The van was comfortable and clean.  The views were amazing.  We would recommend Jared and his tour as 10 out of 10!

review.name: Fun moderate hike
review.reviewBody: Had a great time seeing this beautiful land. And the Snoqualmie falls was especially gun to see as a twin peaks fan. Tour guide was nice as well.

review.name: Book it
review.reviewBody: This tour was so worth it. Twin falls is gorgeous! We could have stayed exploring there all day. Our tour guide, Jearbear was very knowledgable and entertaining

review.name: Great hike, wonderful guide
review.reviewBody:
My husband and I truly enjoyed this hike. Jared was very knowledgeable about the area and provided great info about how the various mountain ranges developed as well as the native flora.  On top of that the views of the falls were amazing and we had the opportunity to tack on some extra hiking. 

Would highly recommend this trip!

review.name: Beautiful fall
review.reviewBody:
Very close to Seattle. Easy walk to an amazing view. Nice gift shop close by. Highly recommend if you are in Seattle
Easy hike if you want to get close to the call.

review.name: Amazing Experience
review.reviewBody: Jared did a fantastic job guiding us during the tour. I would recommend Jared’s tour for any waterfall/ hike enthusiasts!

review.name: Fun morning of hiking and viewing waterfalls
review.reviewBody: Really enjoyed this trip!  Jared was an informative guide and enjoyable to talk to.  The hike was beautiful and we got a good workout making our way up to the first viewing area.  As it was a four hour trip, it worked into well into our schedule.

itemListElement.name: Welcome to Seattle: Private 2.5-hour Highlights Walking Tour

name: Welcome to Seattle: Private 2.5-hour Highlights Walking Tour
description: Visit the best of Seattle with a private guide with you every step of the way. On your private tour, you will explore the waterfront and meander through the historic Pike Market and see the world’s first Starbucks. Then, hop aboard the city’s monorail for a quick transfer a mile up the road. Here, your guide will take you through another pocket of the city’s treasures, as time allows. Your tour finishes with timed-entrance tickets to the Space Needle, where your guide will help you hop in line. Your dual-ticket also gets you entrance for the day to Chihuly Garden and Glass, which is well worth spending a large portion of your day. We suggest taking a little food break before going into the Chihuly museum, as the artwork in there is best explored at your leisure.

review.name: TAKE the guided walking tour.

itemListElement.name: The Bavarian Village of Leavenworth: Day Trip from Seattle

name: The Bavarian Village of Leavenworth: Day Trip from Seattle
description:
Tucked neatly in the foothills of the Cascade Mountain Range is a Bavarian oasis. Central Washington is a geological wonder where old-growth forests meet high-desert landscapes carved from the ice ages. And in the centre of it, all is the small town of Leavenworth. Here, German influence reigns supreme, with classic Bavarian architecture, wonderful gift shops, and authentic German pubs and eateries to sample.

This charming town is located in the heart of the Cascade Mountains in Washington State and was developed in Bavarian-themed architecture that has made it a popular destination for people from all over the world. 

From the moment you arrive, you'll be transported to another world, complete with Alpine-style buildings, traditional German cuisine, and its lively downtown area, which is filled with quaint shops, art galleries, and restaurants.

review.name: Find the Christmas spirit!
review.reviewBody: It is a fun destination for families and couples for a day or two!  We enjoyed our time here looking at shops and bought Christmas ornaments and decorations.  Lot's of places to eat too!

itemListElement.name: Lonely Planet Experiences: Full Day Excursion to Olympic National Park

name: Lonely Planet Experiences: Full Day Excursion to Olympic National Park
description: Enjoy a small group tour to one of America's National Parks, and hike various trails in the Olympic Mountains. On your small group tour (up to 10 guests), you will be driven from Seattle on a scenic trail to the national park, where you will visit several areas of the park. Throughout the day, you will do 3-4 hikes, for a total of about 4.5 miles of gentle to moderate hiking, with as many breaks as you need. You’ll visit scenic Hurricane Ridge, one of the park’s gorgeous overlooks. On a clear day, you can see across the sound to Canada, but even on a cloudy day, there are ample opportunities to interact with the wildlife, including marmots and deer. You’ll visit Marymere Falls and Crescent Lake as well – two other favorite spots in the park. We recommend you dress in layers, and wear hiking boots (though they’re not essential). Please note: the hikes require a minimum level of fitness. You will be dropped off in central Seattle or at your hotel after about 12 hours.

name: Can Can Culinary Cabaret
description: Seattle’s Pike Place Market is home to the world famous Can Can, an intimate 120 seat dinner theatre and production house. The venue's entertainment, food, and drink experience is unmatched. Featuring a menu of French-inspired north west fare sourced from the freshest ingredients from neighboring Market farmers, butchers, and seafood businesses. Experience the gorgeous views of Post Alley and the Puget Sound from the patio of Can Can’s bistro and bar titled, “The Dressing Room.” Moving further into the space, ticketholders will be transported to the theatre.The venue is a romantic space with an interior bathed in art and lush booth seating. At the heart of the institution is the creative team, a professional group of artists who transform the venue with each new show, producing inventive scenic design, choreography, original music, costuming, and more several times each year.
